    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** (74.75) and **Junior Caminero** (72.66) anchoring the lineup. **Yordan Alvarez** remains our premier offensive engine; despite a neutral park adjustment, his elite xwOBA (.393) against Warren guarantees a high floor, while **Junior Caminero** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Bradley, where his dynamic platoon advantage and high-leverage spot in the #2 hole yield an exceptional efficiency score. **Caleb Durbin** also represents a massive \"Strong\" play at 69.42; his aggressive profile against Young is buoyed by a significant 16% SP skill boost, making him a critical source of category production despite his lower batting order position.\n\nWe are paying close attention to speed-reliant options, as our focus remains on stealing every possible advantage in the SB category. **Dillon Dingler** (61.15) earns the start over **Gary Sanchez** primarily due to his matchup against Abbott and the opportunistic potential of a slower opposing delivery, which statistically elevates his SB ceiling. Conversely, **Carson Benge** (48.62) stands as our most difficult omission; he fell just outside the top tier because his park factors and lower lineup placement failed to match the platoon-adjusted production of **Josh Smith** (59.04) or **Hyeseong Kim** (57.80). \n\nRisks today are centered on the bottom of the order, specifically **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (50.93) and **Hyeseong Kim** (57.80), both of whom are confirmed \"Lineup Pending\" entries. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** is particularly vulnerable; should he drop out of the #9 spot or face a defensive replacement mid-game, his efficiency score\u2014already weighed down by a tough matchup against Sheehan\u2014will crater. We are monitoring these lineups closely to ensure **Zac Veen**, **Victor Scott II**, **Lars Nootbaar**, or **Luis Pena** are ready to rotate in if late-breaking reports suggest lower-than-anticipated plate appearances for our current starters. With **Christian Yelich** and **Colt Keith** still sidelined, depth management remains the primary concern for the Zebras.",
